The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, specifically the problem of function computation in a wireless network with a bidirectional relay. This falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of graph theory to characterize the rate region, which could potentially fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
